"ngram\": \"Dujardin\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Federation\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"Equestrian Sports\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"a provisional suspension\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin famously embarked on her dressage career under the tutelage of Hester, who part-owned Valegro, the horse that propelled the rider on to the front pages when the duo secured team and individual gold inLondonback in 2012.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hester_Thrale\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 8.264691373783315e-12, \"text\": \"Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hester_Thrale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hester_Thrale\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her dressage career\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"the tutelage\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 978}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"the front pages\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hester, who will compete forTeam GBnext week, is a signatory to a letter from the board members of the International Dressage Riders Club and posted on their website.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dressage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.449100547312485e-14, \"text\": \"Dressage\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dressage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dressage\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hester\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"forTeam\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"a signatory\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"the board members\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"their website\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The letter read: \\\"The IDRC universally condemn the actions of Charlotte Dujardin as seen in the video footage which was made public this morning by Stephan Wensing from European Equine Lawyers on behalf of his client.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archduke_Charles_Stephen_of_Austria\", \"score\": 0.8177035845035531, \"rank\": 0.2215578122266929, \"text\": \"Stephan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archduke_Charles_Stephen_of_Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archduke_Charles_Stephen_of_Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The letter\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"The IDRC\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"the video footage\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"European Equine Lawyers\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"behalf\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"his client\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Board members are resolute that equine welfare must always be placed uppermost and at all times.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Board members\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"equine welfare\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"all times\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They promote only ethical training methods and practices and strive to encourage all their members to abide by the 'International Equestrian Federation (FEI) Code of Conduct for theWelfareof the Horse' together with all FEI regulations which support and protect equine welfare standards both in and out of competition.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only ethical training methods\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"practices\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"all their members\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"Conduct\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"theWelfareof\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1774}, {\"ngram\": \"the Horse\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"equine welfare standards\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The IDRC Board supports the actions taken by the FEI, the British Equestrian Federation and British Dressage to provisionally suspend Ms Dujardin.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Dressage\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The IDRC Board\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms Dujardin\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It notes that Ms Dujardin has stated she has no excuse for her actions and has also expressed her shame and regret.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms Dujardin\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"no excuse\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"her actions\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"her shame\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"regret\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Due to the live and on-going investigations the Board will not make any further official announcements on this matter until the investigations are concluded.\\\"\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the live and on-going investigations\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"the Board\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"any further official announcements\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\": \"this matter\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"the investigations\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"British Dressage chief executive Jason Brautigam conceded it would be \\\"incredibly difficult\\\" for the team to compete in Paris and also revealed they will conduct their own disciplinary process after Dujardin's actions.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Dressage\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\"}, {\"begin\": 2363, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.7951539788214326, \"rank\": 0.24580709078079394, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}, {\"begin\": 2450, \"end\": 2455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996061888, \"rank\": 3.937388285540132e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"their own disciplinary process\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2522}, {\"ngram\": \"Dujardin's actions\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Contrary to some reports, we did not receive any complaint or have any sight of the video prior to this week,\\\" Brautigam said in a statement on Thursday night.\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2710, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some reports\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"any complaint\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2609}, {\"ngram\": \"any sight\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2627}, {\"ngram\": \"the video\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"this week\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"Brautigam\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday night\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We always protect and support whistleblowers and would encourage anyone with evidence of equine abuse to come forward at the earliest opportunity.\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"whistleblowers\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2784}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 2790, \"to\": 2798}, {\"ngram\": \"equine abuse\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"the earliest opportunity\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2858}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We fully support the FEI in the actions they have taken in response to this incident and have reciprocated the provisional six-month suspension with immediate effect.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 3028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2901}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2929}, {\"ngram\": \"this incident\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2946}, {\"ngram\": \"the provisional six-month suspension\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3005}, {\"ngram\": \"immediate effect\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The individual concerned will be subject to our own disciplinary processes, but we will not be making any further comment on the specifics until the FEI's investigations are complete.\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3180, \"end\": 3183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The individual\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3045}, {\"ngram\": \"our own disciplinary processes\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"any further comment\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"the specifics\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the immediate future we need to rally our support around Carl, Lottie (Fry) and Becky (Moody) as they fly the flag for Team GB in Paris over the next ten days.\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3283, \"end\": 3289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"score\": 0.9999997535838095, \"rank\": 2.4641642267144815e-07, \"text\": \"Lottie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\"}, {\"begin\": 3307, \"end\": 3312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999999988258423, \"rank\": 1.168021061295785e-09, \"text\": \"Moody\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\"}, {\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999925924582077, \"rank\": 5.577939715818948e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3350, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996061888, \"rank\": 3.937388285540132e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the immediate future\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3240}, {\"ngram\": \"our support\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3269}, {\"ngram\": \"Carl\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3281}, {\"ngram\": \"Fry\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"the next ten days\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It will be incredibly difficult for them to compete in such circumstances, but we need to show that we are right behind them all the way, as they aim to bring home medals and showcase the best of our sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3589, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such circumstances\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3455}, {\"ngram\": \"home medals\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A day after horse welfare charity Brooke dropped Dujardin as an ambassador, the prestigious London International Horse Show followed suit.\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"horse welfare charity Brooke\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3631}, {\"ngram\": \"an ambassador\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3665}, {\"ngram\": \"the prestigious London International Horse Show\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3714}, {\"ngram\": \"suit\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The London International Horse Show has made the decision that it would not be appropriate for Charlotte Dujardin to continue in her role as an ambassador for the 2024 edition of the show The annual event held just before Christmas was where Dujardin and Valegro broke world grand prix and freestyle records in 2014 that still stand.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3735, \"end\": 3741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.064553340992325e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3742, \"end\": 3766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Horse Show\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\"}, {\"begin\": 3987, \"end\": 3994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valegro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3788}, {\"ngram\": \"Charlotte\", \"from\": 3826, \"to\": 3835}, {\"ngram\": \"her role\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 3868}, {\"ngram\": \"an ambassador\", \"from\": 3872, \"to\": 3885}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 edition\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3906}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3918}, {\"ngram\": \"The annual event\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"Christmas\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"Dujardin\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3981}, {\"ngram\": \"world grand prix and freestyle records\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Following the recently released historical video footage of Charlotte Dujardin and the ongoing investigation being undertaken by the FEI, the London International Horse Show has made the decision that it would not be appropriate for Charlotte Dujardin to continue in her role as an ambassador for the 2024 edition of the show,\\\" a statement on the show's website read.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4128, \"end\": 4146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}, {\"begin\": 4201, \"end\": 4204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 4210, \"end\": 4216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.064553340992325e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 4217, \"end\": 4241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Horse Show\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_International_Horse_Show\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the recently released historical video footage\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4124}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing investigation\", \"from\": 4151, \"to\": 4176}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4263}, {\"ngram\": \"Charlotte\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4310}, {\"ngram\": \"her role\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4343}, {\"ngram\": \"an ambassador\", \"from\": 4347, \"to\": 4360}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 edition\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4381}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4393}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 4396, \"to\": 4407}, {\"ngram\": \"the show's website\", \"from\": 4411, \"to\": 4429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Horse welfare is always at the forefront of all our activities.\\\"\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Horse welfare\", \"from\": 4438, \"to\": 4451}, {\"ngram\": \"the forefront\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4478}, {\"ngram\": \"all our activities\", \"from\": 4482, \"to\": 4500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twoof Dujardin's sponsors, meanwhile, confirmed they had ended their arrangements with her.\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Twoof Dujardin's sponsors\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4529}, {\"ngram\": \"their arrangements\", \"from\": 4567, \"to\": 4585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dave Derby, chief executive of riding helmets manufacturer Charles Owen, said on Facebook: \\\"We will not be commenting on the specific allegations as there is an ongoing FEI investigation into the matter.\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4597, \"end\": 4607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Derby\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dave Derby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Derby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Derby\"}, {\"begin\": 4656, \"end\": 4663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.7358751711192062, \"rank\": 0.356504216083677, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 4766, \"end\": 4769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.314578613880501e-45, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"chief executive\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4624}, {\"ngram\": \"Facebook\", \"from\": 4678, \"to\": 4686}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific allegations\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4742}, {\"ngram\": \"the matter\", \"from\": 4789, \"to\": 4799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, as a globally-respected brand known for our work in improving rider safety and promoting horse welfare, Charles Owen considers any actual or perceived mistreatment of any horse to be totally unacceptable at any level of the sport.\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 5042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4916, \"end\": 4923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.7358751711192062, \"rank\": 0.356504216083677, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a globally-respected brand\", \"from\": 4815, \"to\": 4841}, {\"ngram\": \"our work\", \"from\": 4852, \"to\": 4860}, {\"ngram\": \"rider safety\", \"from\": 4874, \"to\": 4886}, {\"ngram\": \"horse welfare\", \"from\": 4901, \"to\": 4914}, {\"ngram\": \"any actual or perceived mistreatment\", \"from\": 4939, \"to\": 4975}, {\"ngram\": \"any horse\", \"from\": 4979, \"to\": 4988}, {\"ngram\": \"any level\", \"from\": 5019, \"to\": 5028}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 5032, \"to\": 5041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Charles Owen and Miss Dujardin have had a successful partnership for many years, but while we understand the sentiment of her public statement, we have decided to terminate our sponsorship agreement with Miss Dujardin with immediate effect.\\\"\", \"from\": 5044, \"to\": 5286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5045, \"end\": 5052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.7358751711192062, \"rank\": 0.356504216083677, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Miss Dujardin\", \"from\": 5062, \"to\": 5075}, {\"ngram\": \"a successful partnership\", \"from\": 5085, \"to\": 5109}, {\"ngram\": \"many years\", \"from\": 5114, \"to\": 5124}, {\"ngram\": \"the sentiment\", \"from\": 5150, \"to\": 5163}, {\"ngram\": \"her public statement\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5187}, {\"ngram\": \"our sponsorship agreement\", \"from\": 5218, \"to\": 5243}, {\"ngram\": \"Miss\", \"from\": 5249, \"to\": 5253}, {\"ngram\": \"immediate effect\", \"from\": 5268, \"to\": 5284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Fairfax Saddles, posted on Facebook: \\\"We are shocked and saddened by the video depicting one of the well-know users of our products, Charlotte Dujardin.\", \"from\": 5288, \"to\": 5444, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Facebook\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5327}, {\"ngram\": \"the video\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5370}, {\"ngram\": \"the well-know users\", \"from\": 5388, \"to\": 5407}, {\"ngram\": \"our products\", \"from\": 5411, \"to\": 5423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Welfare of the house is of paramount importance at Fairfax Saddles, and we do not condone this kind of behaviour.\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5498, \"end\": 5505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.059198612893536e-16, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Welfare\", \"from\": 5447, \"to\": 5454}, {\"ngram\": \"the house\", \"from\": 5458, \"to\": 5467}, {\"ngram\": \"paramount importance\", \"from\": 5474, \"to\": 5494}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 5537, \"to\": 5546}, {\"ngram\": \"behaviour\", \"from\": 5550, \"to\": 5559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As a result, we are withdrawing our association with her with immediate effect, but will manage the wind-down of our technical support in a way that does not prejudice the interests of the horses, which are our primary concern.\\\"\", \"from\": 5562, \"to\": 5791, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5574}, {\"ngram\": \"our association\", \"from\": 5595, \"to\": 5610}, {\"ngram\": \"immediate effect\", \"from\": 5625, \"to\": 5641}, {\"ngram\": \"the wind-down\", \"from\": 5659, \"to\": 5672}, {\"ngram\": \"our technical support\", \"from\": 5676, \"to\": 5697}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 5701, \"to\": 5706}, {\"ngram\": \"the interests\", \"from\": 5731, \"to\": 5744}, {\"ngram\": \"the horses\", \"from\": 5748, \"to\": 5758}, {\"ngram\": \"our primary concern\", \"from\": 5770, \"to\": 5789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 5793, \"to\": 5929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 5808, \"to\": 5816}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 5832, \"to\": 5844}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 5848, \"to\": 5856}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 5884, \"to\": 5892}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 5901, \"to\": 5913}]}]}"